Alembic migrations for portfolio-site backend.

## Common commands

All commands run from `backend/` (where alembic.ini lives):

    # Create a new migration from model changes
    python -m alembic revision --autogenerate -m "describe change"

    # Apply pending migrations
    python -m alembic upgrade head

    # Roll back one revision
    python -m alembic downgrade -1

    # Show current revision
    python -m alembic current

    # Show history
    python -m alembic history

## Initial setup for existing databases

The first migration (`19fd54de976f`) applies cumulative schema changes made
via model edits before Alembic was introduced. For a fresh database,
`Base.metadata.create_all()` in the app lifespan creates tables at the
current spec, so you should stamp the DB as already-migrated:

    python -m alembic stamp head

For an existing production database whose schema predates BE-007/010/013/019,
run the migration to bring it current:

    python -m alembic upgrade head

## Database URL

env.py reads `DATABASE_URL` from `app.config.settings`. The `sqlalchemy.url`
field in `alembic.ini` is intentionally blank.
